-- Carlye Adds Three Executives to its Management Committee
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   B a u m g a e r t e l
-- 2013-03-15T11:14:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-15/carlye-adds-three-executives-to-its-management-committee.html
Carlye Group LP added three
executives to its management committee, which develops and
executes the private-equity firm’s corporate strategegy.  They are Michael Arpey, head of fund investor relations;
David Marchick, who runs global external affairs; and Mitch
Petrick, in charge of global market strategies, according to a
statement today from Washington-based Carlyle. They join the
firm’s three founders as well as the chief operating officer,
chief financial officer and general counsel on the committee.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christian Baumgaertel at 
 cbaumgaertel@bloomberg.net  